[SN]TITLE[SN]
Peterborough United 0-4 Bradford City

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
James Hanson's brace helped Bradford to an emphatic win at Peterborough - their first ever victory at the ABAX Stadium.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The Bantams took the lead at the end of the first half when Hanson latched onto Kyel Reid's cross, before Reid doubled their lead after the break.
Hanson connected with James Meredith's inviting ball to head in his second, before Steven Davies converted a Tony McMahon assist to complete the scoring.
The win sees Bradford move up to 11th, joint on points with Posh in 10th.
